I actually have never read Gulliver's Travels, being so familiar with the plot from movie adaptations and not actually being forced to do so in school. Left to my devices I typically gravitate to history and most so-called classics I have read have been assigned reading, but I may read this as a historical document because it is interesting to see what someone in the first part of the 1700s thought was compelling enough to write down. And see why it has remained popular enough that everybody knows the name of Jonathan Swift.

Brian Epstein first met John, Paul, George, and Ringo at a performance in Liverpoolâ€™s Cavern Club in 1961. The Beatleâ€™s began releasing solo projects in the early 70â€™s and after years of contractual dispute, the band was legally disbanded in 1974. In December of 1980, any hopes for a reunion were put to rest upon the premeditated murder of John Lennon in front of his Upper West Side apartment. While the band is no more, their 12 studio albums and 13 EPs have been enjoyed by generations of listeners across the globe.

The Three Martyrs

1. (Obverse and Reverse) 10-Peso banknote from the Philippines during the Third Republic era (1946-1973). This edition of the 10-Peso note was the first and last to depict the three martyred Catholic priests Mariano GoÌmez, JoseÌ Burgoa, and Jacinto Zamora, known collectively as â€œGomBurZaâ€. The Cavite Mutiny of 1872 saw an uprising of Filipino soldiers in the Spanish arsenal of Fort San Felipe in Cavite; the mutineers had hoped it would lead to a national uprising against the Spaniards. Like many rebellions that preceded it, it was swiftly put down. In the wake of the mutiny, the three GomBurZa priests were arrested on charges of subversion. The priests had incurred the wrath of the Spanish authorities previously due to their call for equal rights within the clergy as well as their criticism of Spanish friars. The Spaniards were quick to assume the instigation of the three priests in the failed uprising and sentenced them to death. On February 17, 1862, only two days after their conviction, the priests were executed by way of the brutal garrote at Bagumbayan (today Rizal Park in Manila). Though the uprising in Cavite failed, the event is seen as a crucial point in the growth of Philippine nationalism in the decades after. Dr. JoseÌ Rizalâ€™s novel â€œEl Filibusterismoâ€ is dedicated to the memory of the GomBurZa priests. Series c. 1962-1965.

PKD 25: GALACTIC POT-HEALER (written 1968, published 1969)....though it was written before UBIK, POT-HEALER was actually Phil's last published work of the 60s, and yeah, it's a slight affair compared to other works of this period; it's literally his shortest novel of the 60s and features a pretty straightforward (for Phil) plot and a pretty small cast of characters. Joe Fernwright can heal pottery and is lured to Sirius 5 along with some other bizarre talents to help the enormous alien squid-like creature The Glimmung raise a cathedral that has sunk in the ocean. Phil's really trying to make his usual points about empathy and the nature of humanity here, and thankfully there's enough humor and oddness to keep the story moving (there are actually a number of hilarious lines). The last third of the story explores a kind of group-mind experience that reminds me a bit of Theodore Sturgeonâ€™s More Than Human, and represents a very literal exploration of the empathy/caritas concept. Phil didn't think much of the book, at one point claiming he wished he had never written it! It can't really compete with the other works of this period but it's certainly of a piece with Phil's hallucinogenic 60s novels and worth a read for anyone wanting to immerse themselves in his catalog. This edition was published by Grafton/Panther UK in 1987 and bought by me that year at Forbidden Planet in NYC. As usual with Panther it features another amazing, striking cover, this one by Gino dâ€™Achille. Â                 nyc    ciencefiction

"Hot Take Review." As the quarantine prolongs I decided to look into James Bond spy thriller knock offs. The 1964 movie "Banco Ã  Bangkok pour OSS 117" or "Shadow of Evil" (American Title) is from a French film series called OSS 117.  While I have not viewed all of them this one in particular stood out to me. 
While the film is a James Bond knock off, it retains a suave charm of it's own. One of the biggest aspects I could appreciate about the film was how it takes advantage of its locales. With the picture being shot on location, there's a fascinating juxtaposition of mid century architecture with the jungles and ancient ruins of Thailand. This is accented with rich colors that make it both quintessential and pleasing to watch. Like the Bond films the lead Kerwin Mathews plays the role well and you can tell he tries to make the James Bond archetype into his own. The chemistry he shares with his co-star Pier Angeli is a bit conflicting as it does feel forced, however since it is a spy thriller of the 60's you do want them to get together at the end. 
There are plenty of parts that make the film cheesy but I feel that's what makes it enjoyable to watch. The soundtrack is also well written and is similar to the stylings of Henry Mancini. The film has a jazzy soundtrack with an emphasis on swing, something Mancini incorporated into his composing and arrangements. 
Unlike other knock off films I've watched this one has an actual budget, allowing for a bit of "realism." The interiors are not the best however they're not at the inferior level of films produced by "Asylum." Luckily many sequences of the film are shot around the bustling street of Bangkok or the winding rivers of the jungles. The color palette is rich with greenery and bold with the color choices by both wardrobe and vehicles. 
On an aesthetic level you come away from the film appreciating how much it is visually satisfying. .

Being John Malkovich: 10/10

Another knockout film from the Spike Jonze and Charlie Kaufman combo.
Along with Adaptation, the writing is top notch. Itâ€™s probably one of the most well written movies of the last 50 years. The performances are great especially from John Malkovich and Catherine Keener. I found the story to be more investing and interesting than Adaptation although I enjoy both movies a lot. The concept of the film alone is intriguing with our main character finding a portal that can put you inside the head of John Malkovich for 15 minutes. There is a lot of symbolism with puppets that is well thought out and developed along with small themes of finding your sexuality and childhood trauma. If you like Spike Jonze and Charlie Kaufman or if the premise alone intrigues you, then check this film out

No, this is not the fountain of youth... It's Queen Victoria's Fountain which was built in 1901 by the British to commemorate the Diamond Jubilee of Queen Victoria. .
Although more than a hundred years old, this fountain is still functioning well and is probably the only functioning colonial water fountains in Malaysia. Queen Victoria surpassed George III as the longest reigning monarch in the history of England and Scotland history on 23rd September 1896.
.
The Queen requested at the time that any special celebrations are to be put on hold until 1897 in order to coincide with her Diamond Jubilee which was later made a festival of the British Empire. On the tip of the fountain says 'Victoria Regina 1837-1901, erected by the people of Malacca in memory of a great Queen.
.
The Queen Victoria Fountain is probably one of the last traces of the British colonial era in Malaysia and it symbolizes the glorious days of the British colonization in Malaysia in the yesteryears. .
.
.

Todays, early morning explore 2 waterfalls with Aussie girls,
Tibumana Waterfall and Taman Sari waterfall. 
Tibumana Waterfall is a twin waterfall with 2 adjacent water streams. But when the river water above it is small, there is only one large stream that falls into a waterfall. Under the waterfall there is a pool of water that is not too deep so it is very comfortable if used for swimming.

Taman sari waterfall & natural pool is one of the relatively new tourist sites in Bali. The location is still close to downtown Gianyar. This waterfall has begun to be known by local and tourists. There is two pools that you can use for swim.

I feel like my first year of lifting was a warm up because I felt like I was putting in the time and working hard but not seeing the results. Anyone else feel that way? Then after making some changes to my programming & diet I started to see strength gains & muscle definition. .

So letâ€™s talk about protein first. Then Iâ€™ll do a video next post on how to know you are lifting the right weight. .

Calories determine if you will lose/gain weight. Protein determines your body composition & what you will look like at that new weight. I lost my weight & was just a smaller version of myself. I imagined looking different. My goal was to be strong & I felt like I was skinny fat. It was because I was exercising each day with maybe 50 plus grams of protein per day. No where near what my body needed to grow & sustain muscle. Protein also builds the tissues in your body - organs, hair, skin, and nails etc. Itâ€™s extremely important for overall health and fitness. .

I eat about 140 grams a day. I have protein with a meal or snack every 3 hours. I eat as much whole foods as possible and supplement the rest with my protein shakes. I have a whey concentrate first thing in the morning to get myself in an anabolic state so Iâ€™m burning fat and building muscle. Then later in the day if Iâ€™m still short on my grams I have another shake before bed. I also have a whey isolate protein shake with Ignition my carb source within 30 min post workout. .

Most of my daily protein comes from eggs, chicken, salmon, beans, Greek yogurt then supplemented with protein shakes. .

There is no way Iâ€™m eating that much chicken and eggs in a day. Instead of buying extra bags of chicken to hit my numbers I include my tub of protein powder as part of my monthly grocery bill. .

So proud of this boy I never imagined I would well up at a football game for him landing on his face saving a goal!! Keeping the kids in clubs is bloody hard, being a mum taxi, splitting into two groups coz two kids have matches on the same day, half of them eating their dinner in the car while the others dance, some staying up later than normal so we can help at their hobbies, keeping up with homework, and reading and spellings, school meetings, fundraisers. And at the moment they have no idea what that takes. 5 kids, and two grown ups in this house and we make a pretty good team like that. One day, as adults they will realise what it takes for us to do this day after day, week after week, and I hope they will be proud of how hard we work to keep it this way for them. LET'S WRITE AN ESSAYğŸ’ª.
Writing an essay can be quite overwhelming for some students.
They will think long and hard about it and end up not doing it at all.
Well, it won't be tiring anymore if you follow these 5 simple stepsğŸ˜Š.
.
__
 Pick a topic.
If you're asked to write a general essay, pick a good topic that you're interested in. If there's already a topic set for you, try to think in what aspect do you want to write about. Writing something that interests you is very important so as not to lose focus midway .
__
 BRAINSTORM.
Don't immediately write. Think and outline the general idea about your essay. It's often good to brainstorm together with your friends for idea sharing..
__
 Organize.
Write about the important point first than the less one. Try to use the pattern for every point ; thesis statement, explanation then examples. This way, you will know what to write for every point.
__
 Write in Section.
Decide on how many points do you want to write. Introduction is very important..You can just take a quotes and sayings about the topic.
.
__
 Revise.
After finishing the essay, don't forget to check and revise.
.

Dubai is known for EB110's with SS (Supersport) wheels, here is another car which had export plates on it at the time in Feb-2009.

I do like this BBS wheel as they look so good! I don't know any history of this car, it was at a classic car show near the Burj Khalifa, and as you can see, there was almost no interest in the cars!!! I always found that interesting that in Dubai (from 2000-2010), whenever you went to a track, showroom, car show, it's really quiet. This in sharp contrast to today where spotters swarm every event and make it impossible to get the clean shots! Also, there was never any merchandise or car scale models found in the many malls until late 2000s.

Attempting to â€œstay lowâ€ often causes athletes to bend at the hip. This disrupts the flow of power the athlete is attempting to generate.

The start or â€œ0â€ step requires the athlete to generate force behind their Center of Mass at maximal intent.

The higher the amount of force the athlete applies, the better the angle of projection from the start.

When the athlete is powerful and patient enough to project at an angle of around 45 degrees, what should follow is a gradual rise in body position with every step.

All-new for 2011, the Mitsubishi Outlander Sport was launched in the U.S. The Mitsubishi Outlander Sport is a new model intended for younger buyers and smaller families. It's built on the second generation Outlander chassis with the same wheelbase, but it's 14.6 inches shorter overall. The 2011 Outlander Sport uses the Mitsubishi 2.0-liter engine that's in the base Lancer and with options such as AWD, Rockford Fosgate Premium Audio System and navigation, it also offers a full complement of safety equipment. The Outlander Sport was available in ES and SE trim. Front-wheel drive is standard; all-wheel drive is available on the SE. Both use the 2.0-liter four-cylinder engine. Transmission on the ES is the 5-speed manual, with a 6-step CVT optional. The Air Jordan 14 had a brief NBA stint on the feet of the GOAT. He won his 6th championship with the black and red version nicknamed "Last Shot". Another original edition that became a fan favorite is this version called "Black Toe". It was the first time I can remember that an Air Jordan had the same tooling but different materials on the upper on versions that released simultaneously. Its almost like this type had a more luxe, lifestyle feel, as opposed to the performance crafted ribbed upper version. I first saw this on MJ's feet in the opening sequence of "Michael Jordan To The Max" as he literally appeared to fly while performing a long-distance dunk. The second time I've seen them on his feet is a photo in @ogsneakernerd post where he's being interviewed by the press while he's clearly on the move. While they've been on the feet of many a sneakerhead and ball player, the GOAT's exploits in them make them that much more cool. The Air Jordan line is full of great kicks attached to great moments. These clean pair are a great choice for when we make memorable moments of our own....

Twenty One Pilots - Blurryface(2015)

Columbus Ohio's very own Twenty One Pilots' album Blurryface is pretty good. There are a lot of great things on here that are nice but there are some that are iffy. It's pretty hard to define it as one genre since they do a lot.

Let's talk about the great things on this album. There are a lot of great tracks on here, such as Stressed Out, Ride, Lane Boy, The Judge, Message Man, etc. They're full of catchy song writing, great Instrumentation, good vocals, and a little bit of great lyricism.

The simplistic drumming style of Josh Dun, really does the trick for this album. While he definitely could've done a lot more with what he was dealing with he did just enough to get the job done. Tyler Joseph does a lot on this album and all their other ones. He does vocals, piano, ukulele, bass, and a few other things like some synths. He does a lot but he manages to make it feel as if it's not just him with how much is going on.

Now let's talk about some of the flaws on this album. Now there really isnt that much that I would consider bad but it's not perfect. Some of the songs are borderline obnoxious, like Polarize and Doubt. The vocals are really bland and seem uninspired.

When it comes to instrumentation one word comes to mind...simple. From the drumming to the basslines and even to the ukulele, they manage to keep it extremely simple. Dont get me wrong, this isnt a bad thing. It's just they could've had a lot more and I feel like there are some missing opportunities here for them to really show what they're capable of.

This album is pretty good. Though Twenty One Pilots has recieved a lot of hate and praise, I'm just here to tell my honest opinion on them and others. This is my opinion on them without sugarcoating. Overall I'm feeling a nice 6.5/10

Fav tracks: Stressed Out, Ride, Lane Boy, The Judge, We Don't Believe What's on TV

Least fav tracks: Polarize, Doubt

Success is hard and that means that it will not come easy and as closer you reaching success as more fear you will have from failing.
